Groot2012CensoredGP	InProceedings	true	Groot, Perry and Lucas, Peter	2012	Gaussian Process Regression with Censored Data Using Expectation Propagation	Proceedings of the 6th European Workshop on Probabilistic Graphical Models, PGM 2012				115-122			9788415536574			https://research.utwente.nl/en/publications/gaussian-process-regression-with-censored-data-using-expectation-/	manual_required		No DOI is present; use the University of Twente record or PGM proceedings manually if needed.	sections_en/02_literature_review.tex:278	sections_zh/02_literature_review.tex:284	The broader survival regression literature offers additional tools for censored outcomes: Accelerated Failure Time (AFT) models parameterise the censored outcome under distributional assumptions more flexible than the Gaussian Tobit; inverse probability of censoring weighting (IPCW) approaches re-weight complete cases to account for the censoring mechanism; and Gaussian process regression with censored likelihoods has been developed for exactly this combination of GP modelling and right-censored targets \cite{Groot2012CensoredGP}.	更广泛的生存回归文献为删失结果提供了额外工具：加速失效时间（AFT）模型在比高斯 Tobit 更灵活的分布假设下参数化删失结果；删失逆概率加权（IPCW）通过对完整样本重新加权来校正删失机制；而针对高斯过程建模与右删失目标的组合，也已有 GP 删失似然回归方法被开发出来 \cite{Groot2012CensoredGP}。	Supports Gaussian-process regression with censored observations using expectation propagation.	用于支撑采用期望传播处理删失观测的高斯过程回归方法。	Verified via University of Twente research record; authors, title, PGM 2012 venue, pages, year, abstract, and BibTeX fields confirmed.
