Detlefsen2019VarianceNetworks	InProceedings	true	Detlefsen, Nicki S. and Jorgensen, Martin and Hauberg, Soren	2019	Reliable Training and Estimation of Variance Networks	Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems 32					10.48550/arXiv.1906.03260			1906.03260		https://arxiv.org/abs/1906.03260	manual_required		arXiv/NeurIPS preprint; use the arXiv/DOI link manually or through institutional access if needed.	sections_en/02_literature_review.tex	sections_zh/02_literature_review.tex	For this thesis, the deterministic Stage~1 mean fit is a stabilising step: training a heteroscedastic Gaussian head from scratch can let the variance branch absorb mean errors, down-weight difficult samples, and slow or destabilise the mean fit, a failure mode documented in variance-network and \(\beta\)-NLL studies \cite{Detlefsen2019VarianceNetworks,Seitzer2022PitfallsHeteroscedastic}.	在本文中，确定性 Stage~1 均值预训练是关键稳定化步骤：若从零开始训练异方差高斯输出头，方差分支可能吸收均值误差、降低困难样本权重，并使均值拟合变慢或不稳定，这一失效模式已在方差网络和 \(\beta\)-NLL 相关研究中被记录 \cite{Detlefsen2019VarianceNetworks,Seitzer2022PitfallsHeteroscedastic}。	Documents the instability of training heteroscedastic variance networks from scratch (the variance branch attenuating the mean gradient), motivating the deterministic Stage 1 mean warm-start before NLL training.	记录从零训练异方差方差网络的不稳定性（方差分支削弱均值梯度），为 NLL 训练前先做确定性 Stage 1 均值预热提供依据。	Checked arXiv 1906.03260 and NeurIPS 32 proceedings; variance-network reliability paper supporting the warm-start rationale.
Seitzer2022PitfallsHeteroscedastic	InProceedings	true	Seitzer, Maximilian and Tavakoli, Arash and Antic, Dimitrije and Martius, Georg	2022	On the Pitfalls of Heteroscedastic Uncertainty Estimation with Probabilistic Neural Networks	International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR)					10.48550/arXiv.2203.09168			2203.09168		https://openreview.net/forum?id=aPOpXlnV1T	manual_required		arXiv/OpenReview preprint; use the OpenReview/arXiv link manually or through institutional access if needed.	sections_en/02_literature_review.tex	sections_zh/02_literature_review.tex	For this thesis, the deterministic Stage~1 mean fit is a stabilising step: training a heteroscedastic Gaussian head from scratch can let the variance branch absorb mean errors, down-weight difficult samples, and slow or destabilise the mean fit, a failure mode documented in variance-network and \(\beta\)-NLL studies \cite{Detlefsen2019VarianceNetworks,Seitzer2022PitfallsHeteroscedastic}.	在本文中，确定性 Stage~1 均值预训练是关键稳定化步骤：若从零开始训练异方差高斯输出头，方差分支可能吸收均值误差、降低困难样本权重，并使均值拟合变慢或不稳定，这一失效模式已在方差网络和 \(\beta\)-NLL 相关研究中被记录 \cite{Detlefsen2019VarianceNetworks,Seitzer2022PitfallsHeteroscedastic}。	Identifies the sigma-arbitrage failure of heteroscedastic Gaussian NLL (the target of the beta-NLL fix), where variance inflation discounts the mean gradient; supports warm-starting a deterministic mean before NLL and variance training.	指出异方差高斯 NLL 的 sigma 套利失效（β-NLL 的修正对象）：方差膨胀会折减均值梯度；支持在 NLL 与方差训练前先预热确定性均值。	Checked arXiv 2203.09168 and OpenReview (ICLR 2022); the beta-NLL paper, links confirmed.
